        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2889280888" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14687380026965750833"><a href='https://imgur.com/KuESdtA' rel='nofollow noopener'>
  <img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1617199982i/31110887._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/>
</a><br/>(Throwback Review) This is one of the best medical memoirs I have read. This book tells us about cancer both from a Doctor&apos;s perspective and a patient&apos;s perspective. Kalanithi&apos;s journey from a medical student into a Stanford Neurosurgeon will be an inspiring one for many. But it is the latter half of the book that tells you how to deal with a terminal illness that inspires you the most.<br/><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“There is a moment, a cusp, when the sum of gathered experience is worn down by the details of livi</b></i></blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText14687380026965750833" style="display:none"><a href="https://imgur.com/KuESdtA" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1617199982i/31110887._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a><br>(Throwback Review) This is one of the best medical memoirs I have read. This book tells us about cancer both from a Doctor's perspective and a patient's perspective. Kalanithi's journey from a medical student into a Stanford Neurosurgeon will be an inspiring one for many. But it is the latter half of the book that tells you how to deal with a terminal illness that inspires you the most.<br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“There is a moment, a cusp, when the sum of gathered experience is worn down by the details of living. We are never so wise as when we live in this moment.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote></span>
